discourse_list.title: Starknet - State of the builder ecosystem

content.content: Starknet Regenesis will now start imminently along with the transition to Cairo 1.0.  For more information about the history of the development of the Starknet and the ambition of Cairo going forward, you can watch the talk of Eli Ben-Sasson at Starknet sessions last month. The Starknet bridge has been experimental due to a tight limit (1Mn DAI) and the fact that we have been waiting for Regenesis. Most protocols are holding off post-Regenesis to deploy their work and hence the demand in DAI has stayed flat. However, Regenesis will make DAI on Starknet enter a new phase as liquidity is foreseen to pick up after the migration. The ecosystem is vibrant and a lot of teams are building. In terms of absolute github repository with 10+ stars, Starknet is slightly below Arbitrum, and in terms of growth, Starknet is by far the first rollup.
